> Whether you're cooking for one or the whole gang, this two-course stunner will help
> take the stress out of dinner–and add some luxury to your evening meal. You'll
> start with a savory crostini appetizer topped with whipped ricotta, honey, and
> walnuts. And for the main, fig jam is paired with balsamic vinegar to create a
> tangy pan sauce to drizzle over tender beef tenderloin. Garlicky mashed potatoes
> and caramelized Brussels sprouts are the perfect accompaniments for this dinner
> designed for those of us who enjoy the finer things (and foods!) in life.

== Honey Walnut Crostini ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @Demi-Baguette{1} crosswise into 8 rounds (16 rounds for 4); spread out on a
#baking sheet{} and drizzle with @olive oil{drizzle}. Toast on top rack until
golden brown, ~{5-10%minutes}. (For 4, if necessary, divide rounds between two
baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks.) (Reserve sheet for next step.)

Place @Ricotta Cheese{4%ounce} in a #small bowl{}; whisk in a large drizzle of
@olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread ricotta on toasted
baguette rounds; drizzle with @Honey{4%teaspoon} and sprinkle with
@Walnuts{1/2%ounce}.

Serve with your favorite beverage for snacking while you prepare the rest of the
meal.

> TIP: Prefer to serve the crostini with the main course? Toast now and assemble
> right before serving!

== Mashed Parmesan Potatoes ==

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}.
Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Strip rosemary leaves from
@Rosemary{1/4%ounce} stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings).
Halve, peel, and mince @Shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4).

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Melt @Butter{2%TBSP} in empty pot used for potatoes over medium heat. Add garlic;
cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add drained potatoes and @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}; mash until smooth, adding
splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed with a #potato masher{}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Top with @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon}.

== Toasted Panko ==

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #medium pan{},
preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

== Brussels Sprouts ==

Toss Brussels sprouts on sheet used for crostini with a large drizzle of
@olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and crispy,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Carefully transfer to bowl with toasted panko; toss to combine. Season with half
the minced rosemary, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

== Balsamic Fig Beef Tenderloin ==

While Brussels sprouts roast, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with
paper towels; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat.
Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.
Wipe out pan.

Melt @Butter{1%TBSP} in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot; cook until
fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}, @Fig Jam{1}, @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon},
@water{2%TBSP} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), any resting juices from beef, and remaining
minced rosemary to taste. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide mashed potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and beef between plates. Top beef with
sauce and serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.